  "answer": "**The ghazal \"Dil-e-naadaan tujhe hua kya hai\" (Chapter 36 of *Diwan-E-Ghalib* by Mirza Ghalib) opens with the requested couplet,** which directly addresses the heart's ailment or turmoil:\n\n> My foolish heart, what's led you to this sway?  \n> For this deep pain, what is the healing way? Pray, what is it?[^1]\n\nThis matla (opening couplet) questions what has happened to the \"naive\" or \"foolish\" heart (*dil-e-naadaan*) and seeks the remedy for its suffering, matching your description precisely.[^1]: [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/36-dil-e-naadaan-tujhe-hua-kya-hai/translation/#p-414b38)",
